#. type: Title ====
#, no-wrap
msgid "Internationalization"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Every UI screen is internationalized in {project_name}.  The default "
"language is English, but if you turn on the `Internationalization` switch on "
"the `Theme` tab you can choose which locales you want to support and what "
"the default locale will be.  The next time a user logs in, they will be able "
"to choose a language on the login page to use for the login screens, User "
"Account Management UI, and Admin Console.  The link:{developerguide_link}"
"[{developerguide_name}] explains how you can offer additional languages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#, no-wrap
msgid "User Locale selection"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"In order to select the best possible locale for a user there is a locale "
"selector provider that handles deciding what is the best locale on the "
"information available. One thing to note here is that it is not always known "
"who the user is.  For this reason the previously authenticated users locale "
"is remembered in a persisted cookie."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The logic for selecting the locale uses the first of the following that is "
"available:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"User selected - when the user has selected a locale using the drop-down "
"locale selector"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"User profile - when there is an authenticated user and the user has a "
"preferred locale set"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Client selected - passed by the client using for example ui_locales parameter"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Cookie - last locale selected on the browser"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Accepted language - locale from `Accept-Language` header"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Realm default"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "If none of the above, fallback to English"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"When a user is authenticated an action is triggered to update the locale in "
"the persisted cookie mentioned earlier. If the user has actively switched "
"the locale through the locale selector on the login pages the users locale "
"is also updated at this point."
msgstr ""
